## 2. Automated Implementation

### 2.1 GitHub Actions CI Workflow

**File:** `.github/workflows/ci.yml`

**Purpose:** Quality gates before deployment — lint, type-check, build validation

**Triggers:**
- Push to `dev`, `qa`, `main` branches
- Pull requests targeting `dev`, `qa`, `main`

**Jobs:**
| Job | Purpose | Blocking |
|-----|---------|----------|
| Setup | Install pnpm, Node.js, cache deps | - |
| Lint | ESLint validation | ✅ Yes |
| Type Check | TypeScript validation | ✅ Yes |
| Build | Next.js build validation | ✅ Yes |

**Optimizations:**
- pnpm caching via `setup-node`
- Concurrency control (cancel in-progress on new push)
- 10-minute timeout (prevent stuck jobs)
- Frozen lockfile (consistent installs)

### 2.2 Git Branch Strategy

**Branches to Create:**
| Branch | Purpose | Protected |
|--------|---------|-----------|
| `dev` | Development environment | No |
| `qa` | QA/Staging environment | Yes (recommended) |
| `main` | Production environment | Yes (existing) |

**Creation Commands:**
```bash
# Create dev branch from main
git checkout main
git pull origin main
git checkout -b dev
git push -u origin dev

# Create qa branch from main
git checkout main
git checkout -b qa
git push -u origin qa
```

### 2.3 Environment Variable Documentation

**File:** `.env.example`

Documents all required environment variables with placeholder values and descriptions.

